&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The London Road Medical Centre is a long-established practice located just on the outskirts of Sittingbourne Town Centre, with a great travel network accessing the A249, M2 and M20, There is onsite parking for GP’s, Paramedics and disabled patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our clinical team currently consists of; 1 GP Partner, 2 Salaried GPs, 1 Paramedic Practitioner, 2 Practice Nurses and a phlebotomist, who are supported by the Practice team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our patient population is 7,700, which is spread evenly across all age bands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We use the EMIS Web as our clinical system, with integrated products such as Docman, DXS, Iplato, Lexicom, ECG, 24 hour BP and spirometry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are part of Sittingbourne PCN which has 2 clinical directors, all swale practices communicate and work well together, recently Swale and Medway CCG has merged&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We currently have a vacancy for an enthusiastic, motivated salaried GP for 4 – 8 sessions per week Monday to Friday, starting with us as soon as possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your working day will consist of face to face, telephone, video Consultations, home visits and administration work, Sick notes, Lab Results, prescriptions etc, which time will be allocated for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a competitive salary with 6 weeks annual leave and 1 weeks study leave on a pro-rata basis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss this vacancy or come in for an informal discussion please contact our Practice Manager Lisa&lt;/p&gt;
